ZH: 皇帝是古代中国的统治者。
EN: The emperor was the ruler of ancient China.

ZH: 他是这个朝代的第一位皇帝。
EN: He was the first emperor of this dynasty.

ZH: 皇帝有绝对的权力。
EN: The emperor had absolute power.

ZH: 他向皇帝请愿。
EN: He petitioned the emperor.

ZH: 皇帝住在紫禁城。
EN: The emperor lived in the Forbidden City.

ZH: 皇帝穿着华丽的衣服。
EN: The emperor wore magnificent clothes.

ZH: 皇帝周游国内各地。
EN: The emperor traveled around the country.

ZH: 皇帝持有权杖和王冠。
EN: The emperor held a scepter and a crown.

ZH: 皇帝赐福于臣民。
EN: The emperor bestowed blessings upon his subjects.

ZH: 皇帝宣布终身制。
EN: The emperor declared a lifetime system.

ZH: 皇帝下令征召士兵。
EN: The emperor ordered the recruitment of soldiers.

ZH: 皇帝邀请外交使者。
EN: The emperor invited foreign diplomats.

ZH: 皇帝毫不留情地处死罪犯。
EN: The emperor ruthlessly executed criminals.

ZH: 皇帝在庙宇祭祀祖先。
EN: The emperor worshipped his ancestors in the temple.

ZH: 皇帝发布了皇家布告。
EN: The emperor issued a royal decree.

ZH: 皇帝培养了一支勇猛的军队。
EN: The emperor trained a fierce army.

ZH: 皇帝与权臣争论政策。
EN: The emperor argued with his powerful ministers over policies.

ZH: 皇帝寻觅远方的珠宝。
EN: The emperor sought for jewels from distant lands.

ZH: 皇帝召见智者来商讨道德问题。
EN: The emperor summoned wise men to discuss moral issues.

ZH: 皇帝被称为“天子”。
EN: The emperor was referred to as the "Son of Heaven."
